This paper is about automatic program repair, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of a bot to automatically fix bugs also involves programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The fact that the bot proposes patches to human developers suggests a focus on software development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper's emphasis on the security implications of automatic program repair suggests a possible connection to cryptography (cs.CR).
